Information
Visitors are welcomed at the ETDS at any moment. This means you can have your family come and watch for the competition. You can also have someone from your association join for one of the parties to give them a taste of the ETDS!

There are two types of visitors:
Daytime visitors & Evening visitors.

Because of space limitations we have a limited number of daytime visitor (spectator) tickets and evening visitor tickets available. If you or some of your friends or relatives are interested in coming to watch the tournament, please fill out the registration form.

Keep in mind this is an alcohol-free event and smoking is prohibited at the location.
Furthermore, the Code of Conduct must be followed.
Daytime visitors
Day visitors are welcome during the tournament to come and cheer on their friends and family. Daytime is from 08:30 until the end of the tournament, usually around 19:30.
Evening visitors
Evening visitors are welcome during the evening parties for dancing and watching all shows. You can dance from the start of the evening program until the early morning.
For the exact times per day, see the program.
Food, Drinks
No food or drinks are included in the admission fee. However, food and drinks can be bought at nearby restaurants and shops in the city.

Drinks can be purchased at the bar. Keep in mind that this is a cashless tournament, so you can not pay in cash.

Ordering food to the venue is strictly forbidden.
Signup, Payment
Please register using the visitor form if you want to come watch the tournament or dance all night.
You will receive an email with payment informations withing four days after you sign up to confirm your spots.

Entrance for daytime visitors is €10.
Entrance for evening visitors is €10.
Entrance for daytime & evening is €15.
Entrance for entire weekend is €40.
This does not includes access to the lunch buffet. Drinks are not included and can be purchased at the bar. The confirmation email will contain the payment details.